node.text:
Here at New Belgium, we love two things: beer & vessels for drinking beer. That’s why we’re so excited about our 2021 Artist Series globe glasses from renowned artists Hyland Mather and Cody Hudson. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
These glasses are extra special because it’s our 30th anniversary—and to be honest—we wanted to celebrate with a lil’ glassware birthday gift. It’s our party & we’ll drink if we want to! ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
All jokes aside, Hyland and Cody had such wonderful things to say about their process & design inspiration—and we’re stoked to share their thoughts & glasses with you. Link in bio to purchase them online, or swing by one of our LC's to pick them up.⁠⁠
#newbelgium #artistseries #craftbeer

node.text:
Although beer will be the least of our worries in a full-on climate crisis, we love beer, and we don't want to imagine a world where it tastes like this.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Curious to try it yourself? There's a limited number to order via our link in bio or swing by to pick up a 4-pack at our Asheville or Fort Collins taprooms (now open!).⁠⁠
#newbelgium #thenbeer #forceforgood

node.text:
This Earth Day, we think it’s about time we give big business a last call. 70% of fortune‐500 companies don't have a meaningful plan to address climate change by 2030, and we need these corporations to join us in using their power and influence as a force for good. Because the future of beer could taste pretty bad, and nobody wants that to happen. Hit our link in bio to ask them to commit to climate action now.⁠⁠
#newbelgium #torchedearth #thenbeer #forceforgood

How it started is the stuff of urban legend, but New Belgium is known for the long-standing tradition of gifting employees with a limited edition bike on their one-year anniversary. When it came to building our 30th-anniversary version, we knew a project this special meant calling on the best of the best. @brooklynbikeco and @joshua_ariza of @chompbrand came together and designed a custom bike that embodies our core values and looks damn good doing it, too. Go behind the scenes with the folks responsible for this year’s epic ride. #newbelgium #newbelgium30 #craftbeer⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Want a chance to win one of these bad boys for yourself? Hit our link in bio and enter now!⁠⁠

Brewing good & doing good: since its founding in 2013, we've been a part of @alesforals, and we're so excited for this year's release! Now pouring in our Fort Collins tap room, this West Coast IPA was brewed with Montana Craft Malt and the YCH Ales for ALS hop blend, with a portion of sales going directly to the cause. Ales for ALS is a national fundraising campaign started by a Yakima Valley hop farming family to raise funds and awareness for ALS research at the ALS Therapy Development Institute (ALS TDI). Head to our link in bio to learn more about their story and how they're working to end ALS, and then swing by our taproom for a pint.

node.text: Friends, it is with a heavy heart that we are canceling Tour de Fat 2021 in both Fort Collins and Asheville. At New Belgium we pride ourselves on being a force for good, so we are prioritizing the health of our communities to prevent further community spread of COVID-19. The spiking rates associated with the Delta variant just present too many unknowns at this point. While we’ll miss getting together to celebrate with beers and bemusement, we’ll still be supporting our local bicycle non-profit partners by way of donations. Follow along here and @tourdefat for giveaways and opportunities to further support our local partners in the coming weeks.

node.text:
What do our 1993 Abbey Ale and our 30th Anniversary Wild Ale have in common? Well, besides being kick-ass beers (in our biased opinion) they also show our dedication to “go big or go home” with our brewing.
 
In 1993 our Abbey Ale was the first Belgian beer the @greatamericanbeerfestival had ever seen. Because the brewing process for Belgian beers was so rare in the states, they actually had to make a new category to award it a gold medal. Since then, we’ve been striving to not just make award winning beers—we’ve been striving to make category shattering ones.
 
Cut to the year 2021. We were really swinging for the fences with our 30th Anniversary Wild Ale because we wanted to brew something truly special and world-class to celebrate this milestone. Honestly, this beer was so complex, it took us a few tries to get it right, but we couldn't be happier with the outcome. Maybe someday there will be a five-beer blend category. *wink wink nudge nudge* @greatamericanbeerfestival 
 
#craftbeer #newbelgium #newbelgium30

node.text: Here’s a reason to smile, our Session Sour Oh, Hi! was brewed with fresh Colorado prairie sage to give it a light, almost minty quality. The @oldtownspiceshop right here in Fort Collins was able to source this sage for us just outside of Pagosa Springs where it went directly from the mountainside into our foeders to complement the pixie tangerines from our collaborators @FlyingEmbersBrew in Ojai, California. The result is a perfectly balanced summer refresher that gives back to wildfire relief in Colorado and California. Available now for purchase at select retailers in Colorado and Southern California, along with direct shipping to select states, and in our Fort Collins, Asheville, & SF Liquid Centers. BFFs aka Beer friends forever. Here’s a lil’ fun fact for you: The Town Pump was the first place to have Fat Tire on draft. That means that 30 years ago (almost to the day) the very first draft Fat Tire was poured. It’s pretty wild to reflect on, especially because craft beer and Fort Collins have changed so much since then. But one thing remains the same—the Town Pump, with its decades of bumper stickers, rich wood walls, and an endless supply of Fat Tire.

Continue the journey and head to our link in bio to see the newly unveiled Fat Tire website!
